.TH "pwrdm_disable_hdwr_sar" 9 "pwrdm_disable_hdwr_sar" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pwrdm_disable_hdwr_sar \- disable automatic hardware SAR for a pwrdm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pwrdm_disable_hdwr_sar
.BI "(struct powerdomain *pwrdm "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pwrdm" 12
struct powerdomain *
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Disable automatic context save-and-restore upon power state change
for some devices in the powerdomain \fIpwrdm\fP.  Warning: this only
affects a subset of devices in a powerdomain; check the TRM
closely.  Returns -EINVAL if the powerdomain pointer is null or if
the powerdomain does not support automatic save-and-restore, or
returns 0 upon success.
